What is Networking?
Networking is the process of connecting two or more devices so they can communicate and share data.

How Networking Works
User---DNS---IP---Server


OSI Model

Layer   Name         | Function                              | Example               
 7      Application  | User-facing network services          | HTTP, HTTPS, FTP      
 6      Presentation | Data translation and encryption       | SSL/TLS, JPEG         
 5      Session      | Starts, maintains, ends sessions      | NetBIOS               
 4      Transport    | Reliable delivery and error checking  | TCP, UDP              
 3      Network      | Routing using IP addresses            | IP, ICMP              
 2      Data Link    | Communication within the same network | Ethernet, MAC         
 1      Physical     | Transmits raw bits over the medium    | Cables, Wi-Fi signals 


TCP/IP Model (4 Layers)

Application	     HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, SMTP,     DNS	User services
Transport	       TCP, UDP	                   End-to-end communication
Internet	       IP, ICMP	                   Routing between networks
Network Access	 Ethernet, Wi-Fi	           Sending data over the physical network
